As a developer, I need to perform automated security, quality, maintainability, complexity, and performance scans against Python applications in order to identify vulnerabilities, coding issues, performance bottlenecks, maintainability risks, and non-compliant coding patterns before deployment to higher environments.

The scanning process should provide centralized and structured reports that help developers and engineering teams:

* Detect security vulnerabilities and insecure coding practices
* Identify code quality and linting violations
* Measure code complexity and maintainability metrics
* Detect performance bottlenecks and resource-heavy operations
* Improve coding standards consistency across applications
* Reduce operational and production risks
* Support secure coding and enterprise compliance initiatives
* Enable proactive remediation before production deployment

The solution will leverage automated scanning tools including:

* Scalene
* Ruff
* Pylint
* Radon
* Bandit
* Semgrep

Expected outcome:

* Standardized scanning process across Python applications
* Actionable reports for developers and reviewers
* Improved application stability, security, and maintainability
* Reduced manual review effort and technical debt
